orangelight.title: Figgy object thumbnail and Google Books thumbnail overriding eachother in oranglight catalog record.

comments.body:
In Orangelight, the page to [view the StackMap](https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/99118878653506421/stackmap?loc=arch$stacks&cn=NA1080.R85%20B54%202019) calls the [Firestone Locator](https://github.com/pulibrary/firestone_locator) and embeds the result via an `iframe` with `src` "https://locator-prod.princeton.edu/index.php?loc=arch$stacks&id=99118878653506421&embed=true"

Notice that Orangelight only passes a location code (e.g. "arch$stacks") and an MMS_ID (e.g. "99118878653506421") to the Locator (see code https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/main/app/services/stackmap_service.rb#L48) and this is good enough for the StackMap to work in most cases. 

I suspect internally the Locator fetches the item and gets the call number (since we do not pass it down) and then the Locator gets the map from StackMap. 

This leads me to believe that error is either in StackMap or in the Locator. However since the StackMap finds the map if we give it the call number (see comment above) I am thinking that the issue is in the Locator application but I will need to confirm this with Kevin or Carolyn.

I do not know much (anything really) about the Locator application, but I noticed that it makes a call to "http://library.princeton.edu/searchit/record/$id.json" and I don't think those resolve at all. They are redirected to library.princeton.edu/searchit/record/$id.json and that URL always gives me an error "No route found for GET" -- but this might not be the code that gets executed.

The data here needs updating: https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/main/app/services/stackmap_service.rb#L76

"architecture" should just be "arch"
"engineering" should just be "engineer"

this is causing this conditional to give you the wrong iframe link https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/main/app/services/stackmap_service.rb#L20-L26

Also, more locations to update in this method

https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/804582abf64e980fb589ea05e55ac1dae8ff6280/app/services/stackmap_service.rb#L80-L87

We need to add the "library$" prefix for each of these four locations and strip out the old designation for the library under voyager conventions. For example "scigr" is now "lewis$gr".
And here as well https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/blob/804582abf64e980fb589ea05e55ac1dae8ff6280/app/services/stackmap_service.rb#L89-L91
Thanks @kevinreiss
